menu "Zcash HW Wallet"

config DEBUG_LOG_SECRETS
    bool "Log prefixes of secret-bearing material (DEV ONLY)"
    default n
    help
        When enabled, debug-log prefixes (~8 bytes) of secret-bearing buffers
        such as the BIP-39 seed, sk, ask, nk, and the first BIP-39 word.

        These logs are mirrored to USB CDC ACM1, which is reachable by any
        host that opens /dev/ttyACM1. With repeated signing operations the
        prefixes leak enough material to dramatically narrow brute-force
        search of the spending key.

        MUST be 'n' for any build that handles real ZEC. Only enable when
        actively diagnosing a derivation/signing issue on a throwaway seed.

        Tracked in docs/security-audit/03-firmware-esp32.md C-5, L-8.

endmenu
